efore reaching the precise location. If you have a four-wheel vehicle, this may be done with ease. Three step-by-step waterfalls can be found at this location, and they have skillfully cut their own paths through the surrounding rocks. Mountain hiking is another activity that is enjoyable here. If you intend to visit this location, don't forget to bring hiking boots. The water flowing in these falls is very cold, in part because it is shielded from the sun on all sides. Viewing the photos shot there will help you learn more about the location, rest assured. The closest airports are Biju Pattnaik International Airport in Bhubaneswar and Swami Vivekananda International Airport in Raipur. Jarsuguda is the name of the closest railroad station, and it is around 75 kilometers away. 3. Maa Ghanteswari Temple In Sambalpur, Maa Ghanteswari Temple is among the most revered and stunning locations. Bells (Ghanti), as the name suggests, are present everywhere. Following the realization of their wishes, people present Maa with bells. Every day, many pilgrims from all around the state come to this location. This is referred to as the Chipilima Heart (a beautiful picnic spot). The unique feature of this temple area?and the only one of its sort in Orissa?is the tens of thousands of bells that dangle everywhere. The Maa Ghanteswari Temple is situated along the banks of the Mahanadi River, 33 kilometers southwest of Sambalpur. In the past, it had a significant impact on navigation. It was referred to be a lighthouse devoid of light. The goddess Ghanteswari gave the location its name. The navigators were made aware of this tremorous site and avoided it because there used to be some large bells in this location that were producing a loud sound with the help of the wind. Due to the convergence of three separate Mahanadi River streams, the water current in this place is extremely turbulent and forms a vortex. As a result, numerous vessels perished as they approached this location. Swami V